  <span id="freeText743430897461289014" style="display:none">This is not the dark, sketchy, literary Auster. Instead this is the Auster who draws detailed characters, tells wonderful baseball anecdotes and paints the world with light and colour. This is the Auster of 4 3 2 1 and The Brooklyn Follies. <br /><br />I love this Auster.<br /><br />That's not to say I liked the ending; I did not. But I like to think that Miles saw sense, followed his father's advice, and that it all worked out in the end. I believe in the redemptive power of hope.</span>
